  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process Quality Engineer (ISO 13485)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Develop, implement, and maintain QMS in compliance with ISO 9001, ISO 13485, GMP and applicable regulatory requirements; monitor regulatory changes and update systems accordingly.</li><li>Lead internal audits and support external audits (certification bodies, customers, suppliers); act as Management Representative and primary point of contact for certifying authorities.</li><li> Report QMS performance to top management, lead Management Reviews, and drive follow-up actions for continual improvement</li><li>Analyze product quality data and recurring complaints, partner with Operations and Technology teams to address root causes, and provide on-the-floor quality support and coaching.</li><li>wn CCAR and SCAR processes, ensuring data-driven root cause analysis, effective corrective actions, and cross-functional collaboration for timely resolution</li><li>Support global quality initiatives, systems, and tools; ensure local QMS alignment with global standards, share best practices, and support quality contracts and customer documentation.</li></ul><p><br />Requirements:<br /></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Business, Science</li><li>At least 4 years of Process Quality experience</li><li>ISO13485 knowledge</li></ul><p><br />Account Manager:<br />Kerwin Tan Kai Bin (R1331624)<br />kerwin.tan@searchasia.com.sg<br />EA16S8107</p>",
